<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="64" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,284,1030]" box="[264,401,284,310]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,284,1030]" box="[312,511,324,350]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">External features</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,284,1030]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Massive–lobulose with an unarmoured microconulose surface. Each conule ends in a thin projecting fibre (
<figureCitation box="[517,583,404,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. P" captionStartId="2.[264,368,1759,1783]" captionTargetBox="[300,1295,745,1758]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[264,1323,744,1758]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. P. nigra: (A) holotype preserved in alcohol, (B) primary fibres (double arrow) with foreign debris and a network of secondary fibres (arrow), (C) laminated secondary fibres with longitudinal ripples, (D) choanosome with considerable amounts of foreign debris (arrows). SEM" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/172426/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[572,583,404,430]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Consistency stony, incompressible. Oscules spread on the surface, 
<number box="[363,373,444,470]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
–2.8 mm in diameter. Colour blackish outside, beige inside, in alcohol.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,284,1030]" box="[312,414,484,510]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Skeleton</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,284,1030]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Reticulate with a dense network of secondary fibres forming meshes 
<quantity box="[1152,1290,524,550]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.525" metricValueMax="2.25" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" unit="m" value="152.5" valueMax="225.0" valueMin="80.0">80–225 m</quantity>
in diameter. They form fenestrate plates when they join the primary fibres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,284,1030]" box="[312,1304,604,630]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Primary fibres: 
<quantity box="[495,645,604,630]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.725" metricValueMax="7.9" metricValueMin="3.55" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" unit="m" value="572.5" valueMax="790.0" valueMin="355.0">355–790 m</quantity>
in thickness, strongly cored by foreign debris (
<figureCitation box="[1205,1271,604,630]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. P" captionStartId="2.[264,368,1759,1783]" captionTargetBox="[300,1295,745,1758]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[264,1323,744,1758]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. P. nigra: (A) holotype preserved in alcohol, (B) primary fibres (double arrow) with foreign debris and a network of secondary fibres (arrow), (C) laminated secondary fibres with longitudinal ripples, (D) choanosome with considerable amounts of foreign debris (arrows). SEM" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/172426/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[1260,1271,604,630]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,284,1030]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Secondary fibres: 
<quantity box="[537,664,644,670]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" unit="m" value="50.0" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="20.0">20–80 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[685,760,644,670]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[264,367,1091,1115]" captionTargetBox="[338,1281,284,1090]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[307,1281,272,1090]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Light microscope pictures of the secondary skeleton of (A) P. nigra, (B) P. pharmamari, (C) laminated secondary fibres of P. nigra, (D) laminated secondary fibre of P. pharmamari." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/172428/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[746,760,644,670]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A), laminated and completely free of foreign debris. (
<figureCitation box="[360,425,684,710]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. P" captionStartId="2.[264,368,1759,1783]" captionTargetBox="[300,1295,745,1758]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[264,1323,744,1758]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. P. nigra: (A) holotype preserved in alcohol, (B) primary fibres (double arrow) with foreign debris and a network of secondary fibres (arrow), (C) laminated secondary fibres with longitudinal ripples, (D) choanosome with considerable amounts of foreign debris (arrows). SEM" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/172426/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[415,425,684,710]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B–C &amp; 
<figureCitation box="[522,591,684,710]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[264,367,1091,1115]" captionTargetBox="[338,1281,284,1090]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[307,1281,272,1090]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Light microscope pictures of the secondary skeleton of (A) P. nigra, (B) P. pharmamari, (C) laminated secondary fibres of P. nigra, (D) laminated secondary fibre of P. pharmamari." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/172428/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[576,591,684,710]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Through SEM, the surface of the secondary fibres appears rippled in a longitudinal direction (
<figureCitation box="[674,741,724,750]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. P" captionStartId="2.[264,368,1759,1783]" captionTargetBox="[300,1295,745,1758]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[264,1323,744,1758]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. P. nigra: (A) holotype preserved in alcohol, (B) primary fibres (double arrow) with foreign debris and a network of secondary fibres (arrow), (C) laminated secondary fibres with longitudinal ripples, (D) choanosome with considerable amounts of foreign debris (arrows). SEM" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/172426/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[729,741,724,750]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,284,1030]" box="[312,670,764,790]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Tertiary fibres: Very thin, rare.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,284,1030]" box="[312,1218,804,830]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Choanosome containing abundant sand and other foreign materials (
<figureCitation box="[1111,1177,804,830]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. P" captionStartId="2.[264,368,1759,1783]" captionTargetBox="[300,1295,745,1758]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[264,1323,744,1758]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. P. nigra: (A) holotype preserved in alcohol, (B) primary fibres (double arrow) with foreign debris and a network of secondary fibres (arrow), (C) laminated secondary fibres with longitudinal ripples, (D) choanosome with considerable amounts of foreign debris (arrows). SEM" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/172426/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[1166,1177,804,830]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,284,1030]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Distribution: Southwest Pacific region, 
<collectingCountry box="[802,990,844,870]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
islands, from 
<quantity box="[1177,1323,844,870]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" unit="m" value="24.0" valueMax="38.0" valueMin="10.0">10 to 38 m</quantity>
depth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,284,1030]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Note. The re–examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[697,799,924,950]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">holotype</typeStatus>
allowed us to measure the skeletal elements, and our results provide larger fibre diameters (particularly for the primary fibres) from those given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergquist" box="[442,644,1004,1030]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" refString="Bergquist, P. R. (1995) Dictyoceratida, Dendroceratida and Verongida from New Caledonia Lagoon (Porifera: Demospongiae). Memoirs of the Queensland Museum, 38, 1 - 51." type="journal article" year="1995">
Bergquist (
<number box="[571,635,1004,1030]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
